[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] The final results now shown are based on the general Cauchy sum formulas.
[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] The Jacobi theta function is the fundamental solution of the one-dimensional heat equation with spatially periodic boundary conditions.
[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] General solutions of the spatially periodic initial value problem for the heat equation may be obtained by convolving the initial data at *t* = 0 with the theta function.
[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] The Jacobi theta function is invariant under the action of a discrete subgroup of the Heisenberg group.
[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] This invariance is presented in the article on the theta representation of the Heisenberg group.
[src:elliptic-functions/theta-function-p01] with the sum extending over the lattice of integers $\mathbb {Z} ^{n}$ .
